title: A Popular History of Ireland: from the Earliest Period to the Emancipation of the Catholics, Book 12
creator: Thomas D'Arcy McGee
description: LibriVox recording of A Popular History of Ireland from the Earliest Period to the Emancipation of the Catholics, Book 12, read by Sibella Denton. Thomas D'Arcy McGee was an Irish refugee and a father of the Canadian confederation. His work on Irish history is comprehensive, encompassing twelve books; Book 10 subtitled “From the Union of Great Britain and Ireland to the Emancipation of the Catholics”, addresses the period of the creation of the United Kingdom to the granting of religious freedom in Ireland. (Summary by Sibella Denton) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org M4B audiobook of Complete Series
